
                                            SuperSport United were unable to score the one goal they needed to win the final, which was played over two legs.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - TP Mazembe have beaten SuperSport United 2-1 on aggregate to capture the CAF Confederation Cup over two legs. The second leg of the final ended 0-0 in Atteridgeville on Saturday night. Each team had a player sent off in the final 10 minutes of a scrappy encounter. The visitors had Chongo Kabaso sent to the changeroom after he received two yellow cards, while Thuso Phala was shown a straight red for a dangerous tackle. The first leg, played in Lubumbashi, ended 2-1 in Mazembe's favour. The team from the Democratic Republic of Congo have won their third continental trophy in as many years.